article.headline: Ind.-Pur.-Ft. Wayne 97, W. Illinois 95, 5OT
article.story: MACOMB, Ill. (AP) -- It took five overtimes, but IPFW eventually prevailed 97-95 over Western Illinois on Tuesday night. IPFW held a 32-25 lead at halftime, before the Leathernecks fought back to pull even in the second. In the final overtime, IPFW outscored Western Illinois 11-9. Ten players in all managed to get into double digits, with the Leathernecks' David Jackson leading all scorers with 32 point. He also had 12 rebounds. Sammy Hunter added 18 points, Jerryck Owens-Murrey had 16 and Morris Smith came off the bench to chip in 12 for Western Illinois (2-2). The Mastodons (2-3) were led in scoring by Tyler Best and Justin Hawkins, who both had 19 points. Best also pulled down a game-high 17 rebounds. Among the other top scorers for IPFW were Kyle Savely, who had 16 points, and Quintin Carouthers, with 14. IPFW's Jakari Johnson and DeWitt Scott each had 11.
